    {
        "content": "<p>I've been struggling to understand whether this is another case where we should treat junk values as 0 (like defining 1/x to be 0 for x = 0) or whether it would be good to use with_top pnat if the API was more developed, this case feels somehow different to the usual junk value story but i can't put my finger on why...</p>",
